  [David Schwartz]
> > This is already prohibited by the GPL. In fact, most of the
> > difference between GPL software and PD software is that GPL
> > software may not be integrated with non-GPL software.
[Matthew Kirkwood]
> No.  GPL software may not be integrated with non-GPL-compatible
> software.  That's a significant difference, when the no-ads BSD
> licence and the MIT licence are both GPL compatible.
In my opinion this distinction is moot, because of the nature of the
GPL itself.  The act of distributing GPL-compatibly-licensed software
integrated with GPL software *makes* the whole thing GPL-licensed.
